Making an effort to get up and get dressed even if it just meant walking around the house in her favourite pair of heels for a few hours, Kim was motivated to keep moving.

'I think it's just an amazing way to connect, people talk about bullying but I haven't experienced any of that.

'The thing is about getting up and getting dressed and being happy.

'I guess I just want people to do what makes them happy, everyone has something that makes them happy and I don't want cancer to take that away from them', Kim said.

